    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="402"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/2890: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-08T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 8, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>493. Your 530, June 26, 7 p.m.<note n="28" xml:id="d402fn28">Not printed.</note>
                    You are authorized to inform the President that the War and Navy Departments
                    would like to negotiate with the Ecuadoran Government an agreement for the use
                    during the emergency of the Galápagos Islands along the lines of the <pb
                        facs="0390" n="376" xml:id="pg_376"/> agreement relating to Salinas, and
                    inquire whether that is agreeable to him.</p>
                <p>Please report the outcome of this conversation only to the Department. If the
                    President expresses any views regarding the provisions of the new agreement
                    different from the general lines of the Salinas agreement please report these
                    fully.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
